<br>
Sideboard<br>
4 Ghastly Demise<br>
4 Slay<br>
4 Gainsay<br>
3 Chainer&#39;s Edict   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is a deck that is built around one strategy. Decking your opponent, before he can kill you. The way the deck accomplishes this is by countering every spell the other player tries to play and by bouncing everything it gets into play then it uses Traumatize and Haunting Echoes. Even though this combo is not a required combo to get a kill with this deck. Guiltfeeder also can kill your opponent really quick if his graveyard is large enough which is almost always the case anyways because the feeder is a late game kill anyways. Then whole strategy this deck is built around is stoping your opponant and then hurting him with one of the many weapons in your arsenal. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
